  <font color=white>
  Download / Compile
  </font>
 </table>

To compile from source you need<br>
* a 2.6 kernel or a 2.4.20 or newer kernel <br>
* gtk+ 2.4 header files/static libs (libgtk+2.4_1-devel RPM, libgtk-2.0-dev debian)<br>
* gtkmm 2.4 header files/static libs (libgtkmm2.4_1-devel RPM, libgtkmm-2.4-dev debian)<br>
* libiw v27 header files/static libs (libiw27-devel RPM)<br>
<br>
Download the source tarball from the <a href="http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=57022">Sourceforge File List</a><br>
<br>
darcs users can get the source from the read-only darcs repository with:<br>
darcs get http://apradar.sourceforge.net/darcs/apradar<br>
<br>
Here is a quick compatibility test: run 'iwlist eth1 scanning', if that works, ap radar should work too.
<br>

